# #!/usr/bin/env python3
“””
scan_owncloud.py

Phase 1: Peter J Ryan Photography – ownCloud Folder Scanner

Connects to Peter’s ownCloud instance via WebDAV and walks the
“Peter’s Photos” directory, outputting:

1. A human-readable tree report  (folder_report.txt)
1. A machine-readable JSON file  (folder_structure.json)

These outputs are used to decide which folders/files to include
or exclude before building the photo pipeline and website.

## Usage

```
pip install requests
python scan_owncloud.py

# Or supply credentials on the command line (overrides the
# constants defined below):
python scan_owncloud.py --username pryan --password YOUR_PASSWORD
```

## Configuration

Fill in OWNCLOUD_PASSWORD below, or pass it as a CLI argument.
Everything else is pre-configured for Peter’s setup.
